    "body": "I will postpone this until hopefully, I get some help to figure out a simple fix to the current issues described in the fix attempt [PR #832](https://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/pull/832).\r\n\r\nOtherwise, this will require more extensive refactoring of `StatusChatListAndCategories` component which doesn't seem trivial given the complexity and the features it has.\r\n\r\n> Clicking on a category should toggle it\r\n\r\nThe current implementation works while clicking on the title. As soon as I try to process the empty space message the underlying overlapping `MouseArea`s have side effects and make the second item always reproducible.\r\n\r\nAfter spending more time understanding the implementation of `StatusChatListAndCategories` I don't see a simple fix to the current code which is fragile and relies on some workarounds. \r\n\r\n> Clicking on + and ... buttons should NOT toggle the category and should work as expected\r\n\r\nI can't easily reproduce this on the latest master but as soon as I try to fix the first request this is always reproducible.",
